  }, "Event banner")), mdx("p", null, "I formulated the very first post in a personal spirit. Notice that the picture shows a girl dreaming and thinking. The text looked something like this: \u201CStories rule the world. Did you experience the moment when you were afraid to say something? That\u2019s what Toastmasters is about, too. Overcoming your fear is half the battle\u2026\u201D"), mdx("p", null, "And so I gradually bridged Matthew and introduced him, so far only in hints \u2014 how long he\u2019d been working in Toastmasters, how he\u2019d improved as a leader, found his dream job, and how he makes a living. I also mentioned that he hosted a conference in Ko\u0161ice that several guests might know. It could also entice them to come and see us. I ended the whole post with his statement, which is in the header of each of his e-mails."), mdx("blockquote", null, mdx("p", {
